      "text": "Stallman has regularly given a talk entitled \"Copyright vs. Community\" where he reviews the state of DRM and names many of the products and corporations which he boycotts. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "eafd376330ad1f35",
      "text": "His approach to DRM is best summed up by the FSF [[Defective by Design]] campaign. In the talks, he makes proposals for a \"reduced copyright\" and suggests a 10-year limit on copyright. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2c67d9ea97c175d6",
      "text": "He suggests that, instead of restrictions on sharing, authors be supported using a tax, with revenues distributed among them based on [[cubic root]]s of their popularity to ensure that \"fairly successful non-stars\" receive a greater share than they do now (compare with [[private copying levy]] which is associated with proponents of strong copyright), or a convenient anonymous [[micropayment]] system for people to support authors directly. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "abc4cacdac107388",
      "text": "He indicates that no form of non-commercial sharing of copies should be considered a copyright violation. He has advocated [[civil disobedience]] in a comment on [[Ley Sinde]] - [http://torrentfreak.com/richard-stallman-opts-to-disobey-anti-piracy-law-110610/ torrentfreak.com]"
