        "id": "c75e0abd1dbf94c6d352dd177f590bcc",
        "text": "Stallman has regularly given a talk entitled \"Copyright vs. Community\" where he reviews the state of DRM and names many of the products and corporations which he boycotts. His approach to DRM is best summed up by the FSF [[Defective by Design]] campaign. In the talks, he makes proposals for a \"reduced copyright\" and suggests a 10-year limit on copyright. He suggests that, instead of restrictions on sharing, authors be supported using a tax, with revenues distributed among them based on [[cubic root]]s of their popularity to ensure that \"fairly successful non-stars\" receive a greater share than they do now (compare with [[private copying levy]] which is associated with proponents of strong copyright), or a convenient anonymous [[micropayment]] system for people to support authors directly. He indicates that no form of non-commercial sharing of copies should be considered a copyright violation.[ ][ ] He has advocated [[civil disobedience]] in a comment on [[Ley Sinde]].<ref name=\"elpais-leysinde\"/>[http://torrentfreak.com/richard-stallman-opts-to-disobey-anti-piracy-law-110610/ Richard Stallman Opts to Disobey Anti-Piracy Law]"
